{"title_page": "Diego Rico", "text_new": "{{Spanish name|Rico|Salguero}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Diego Rico\n| image = \n| fullname = Diego Rico Salguero<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/844127|title=2018/19 Premier League squads confirmed|publisher=Premier League|date=3 September 2018|accessdate=4 September 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|2|23|df=y}}<ref name=Profile>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/diego-rico_prs369715/person.shtml|title=Diego Rico|publisher=[[Eurosport]]|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Burgos]], Spain<ref name=Profile/>\n| height = 1.81 m<ref name=Profile/>\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Left back]]\n| currentclub = [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|AFC Bournemouth]]\n| clubnumber = 21\n| youthyears1 = 2000\u20132011 | youthclubs1 = [[CD Burgos Promesas 2000|Burgos Promesas]]\n| youthyears2 = 2011\u20132012 | youthclubs2 = [[Real Zaragoza|Zaragoza]] \n| years1 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs1 = [[Real Zaragoza B|Zaragoza B]] | caps1 = 17 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2013\u20132016 | clubs2 = [[Real Zaragoza|Zaragoza]] | caps2 = 106 | goals2 = 5\n| years3 = 2016\u20132018 | clubs3 = [[CD Legan\u00e9s|Legan\u00e9s]] | caps3 = 51 | goals3 = 3\n| years4 = 2018\u2013 | clubs4 = [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|AFC Bournemouth]] | caps4 = 33 | goals4 = 0\n| club-update = 9 February 2020\n}}\n'''Diego Rico Salguero''' (born 23 February 1993) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left back]] for {{English football updater|AFCBourn}} club [[A.F.C. Bournemouth]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Zaragoza===\nBorn in [[Burgos]], [[Castile and Le\u00f3n]], Rico graduated from local [[CD Burgos Promesas 2000]]'s youth system, where he started playing as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] in the [[Five-a-side football|seven-a-side]] variation and later [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vavel.com/es/futbol/2014/01/28/real-zaragoza/323468.html|title=Entrevista. Diego Rico: \"He llegado hasta aqu\u00ed, pero ahora lo dif\u00edcil es mantenerse. Por eso trabajo duro cada d\u00eda\"|trans-title=Interview. Diego Rico: \"I've come this far, but the hardest thing now is to stay there. That's why I work hard every day\"|publisher=[[Vavel]]|first1=Natalia|last1=Hungr\u00eda|first2=Patricia|last2=Lamb\u00e1n|language=es|date=28 January 2014|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref> In June 2011, he joined [[Real Zaragoza]] and was assigned to the ''Juvenil'' squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.burgospromesas.com/secciones/noticias/diego-rico-dejara-el-equipo-de-su-vida-para-fichar-por-el-real-zaragoza|title=Diego Rico dejara el equipo de su vida para fichar por el Real Zaragoza|trans-title=Diego Rico will leave his lifelong club to sign for Real Zaragoza|publisher=Burgos Promesas 2000|language=es|date=4 June 2011|accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nRico made his senior debut with [[Real Zaragoza B|the reserves]], in [[2011\u201312 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2011\u201312]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.heraldo.es/noticias/deportes/futbol/real_zaragoza/2012/07/11/el_zaragoza_inicia_este_jueves_pretemporada_195391_611027.html|title=El Zaragoza B inicia este jueves la pretemporada|trans-title=Zaragoza B start pre-season this Thursday|newspaper=[[Heraldo de Arag\u00f3n]]|language=es|date=11 July 2012|accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref> He served mostly as a backup in his two seasons with the squad, [[2012\u201313 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|the second ending in relegation]].\n\nIn the summer of 2013, Rico was promoted to the main squad and quickly overtook the habitual starter [[Abraham Minero]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vavel.com/es/futbol/2016/07/07/real-zaragoza/666897-abraham-minero-cedido-al-levante.html|title=Abraham sale cedido al Levante|trans-title=Abraham goes out on loan to Levante|publisher=Vavel|first=Javier|last=Gimeno|language=es|date=7 July 2016|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref> On 10 September he played his first match as a professional, starting in a 0\u20131 away loss against [[Deportivo Alav\u00e9s]] in [[2013\u201314 Copa del Rey|the second round]] of the [[Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2013/09/10/futbol/copa_rey/1378841253.html|title=Borja Viguera noquea al Zaragoza en el a\u00f1adido|trans-title=Borja Viguera knocks out Zaragoza in injury time|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=10 September 2013|accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref> He first appeared in the league four days later, playing the full 90 minutes of a 3\u20130 home victory over [[CD Tenerife]] in the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2013/09/14/futbol/2adivision/1379182161.html|title=El Zaragoza estrena su casillero de victorias con una goleada|trans-title=Zaragoza open winning box with a rout|newspaper=Marca|language=es|date=14 September 2013|accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 November 2013, Rico signed a five-year contract to stay at [[La Romareda]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realzaragoza.com/noticias/39853|title=Acuerdo para la renovaci\u00f3n del contrato de Diego Rico con el Real Zaragoza|trans-title=Agreement for Diego Rico's contract renewal with Real Zaragoza|publisher=Real Zaragoza|language=es|date=19 November 2013|accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref> He scored his first professional goal the following month, the first of a 2\u20131 home win against [[C\u00f3rdoba CF]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2013/12/08/futbol/2adivision/1386531606.html|title=El Zaragoza se acerca a los puestos de ascenso|trans-title=Zaragoza get closer to the promotion places|newspaper=Marca|language=es|date=8 December 2013|accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nRico agreed to a new professional deal on 7 January 2016, becoming a full member of the first team and being assigned the {{abbr|no.|number}} 22 jersey.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realzaragoza.com/noticias/54996|title=Diego Rico firma contrato profesional y a partir de ahora llevar\u00e1 el dorsal 22|trans-title=Diego Rico signs professional contract and will wear the 22 jersey from now on|publisher=Real Zaragoza|language=es|date=7 January 2016|accessdate=8 January 2016}}</ref> He finished [[2015\u201316 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|the campaign]] with one goal<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20151011/54438038481/1-3-el-zaragoza-vence-al-albacete-en-25-minutos-primorosos.html|title=1\u20133. El Zaragoza vence al Albacete en 25 minutos primorosos|trans-title=1\u20133. Zaragoza defeat Albacete in 25 immaculate minutes|newspaper=[[La Vanguardia]]|language=es|date=11 October 2015|accessdate=28 April 2017}}</ref> in 39 matches, contributing to an eighth-place finish.\n\n===Legan\u00e9s===\nOn 17 August 2016, Rico joined [[La Liga]] side [[CD Legan\u00e9s]] on a four-year contract<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deportivoleganes.com/noticia/diego-rico-juventud-y-potencia-para-el-lateral-izquierdo-pepinero-hasta-2020|title=Diego Rico, juventud y potencia para el lateral izquierdo pepinero hasta 2020|trans-title=Diego Rico, youth and power to the left ''pepinero'' left flank until 2020|publisher=CD Legan\u00e9s|language=es|date=17 August 2016|accessdate=17 August 2016}}</ref> for a rumoured fee of [[Euro|\u20ac]]1 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/leganes/2016/08/17/57b4187046163fc16f8b4590.html|title=Diego Rico llega al Legan\u00e9s por un mill\u00f3n de euros|trans-title=Diego Rico arrives at Legan\u00e9s for one million euros|newspaper=Marca|first=Sonia|last=Gaudioso|language=es|date=17 August 2016|accessdate=17 August 2016}}</ref> He made his debut in the competition five days later, starting and in a 1\u20130 away win against [[RC Celta de Vigo]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2016_17/la-liga/jornada_1/cel_leg/|title=Estreno de oro del Legan\u00e9s en Primera|trans-title=Golden debut of Legan\u00e9s in ''Primera''|publisher=Marca|first=Borja Luis|last=Callero|language=es|date=22 August 2016|accessdate=22 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nRico scored his first goal in the [[Spanish football league system|Spanish top flight]] on 11 September 2016, but in a 1\u20132 loss at [[Sporting de Gij\u00f3n]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2016_17/la-liga/jornada_3/spo_leg/|title=El Sporting se lleva la victoria ante un Legan\u00e9s combativo|trans-title=Sporting take win against fighting Legan\u00e9s|newspaper=Marca|first=\u00cd\u00f1igo|last=Fern\u00e1ndez|language=es|date=11 September 2016|accessdate=3 September 2018}}</ref> The following 7 August, he agreed to an extension until 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deportivoleganes.com/noticia/diego-rico-renovado-hasta-2021|title=Diego Rico, renovado hasta 2021|trans-title=Diego Rico, renewed until 2021|publisher=CD Legan\u00e9s|language=es|date=7 August 2017|accessdate=8 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n===AFC Bournemouth===\nOn 24 July 2018, Rico was transferred to [[A.F.C. Bournemouth]] for an undisclosed fee, and signed a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.afcb.co.uk/news/first-team/cherries-complete-rico-swoop|title=Cherries complete Rico swoop|publisher=A.F.C. Bournemouth|date=24 July 2018|accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref> He made his debut in the [[Premier League]] on 1 September, playing the entire 0\u20132 away defeat against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45305231|title=Chelsea 2\u20130 AFC Bournemouth|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|first=Neil|last=Johnston|date=1 September 2018|accessdate=3 September 2018}}</ref> He struggled to regularly cement his position in the team during [[2018\u201319 A.F.C. Bournemouth season|his first season]], making just 16 total appearances in all competitions; manager [[Eddie Howe]] later commented that the player had faced some hurdles in settling into the league, with the language barrier and increased physicality of the competition being key factors in this, although he did add that \"he has got the technical quality and [he] has got a lovely left foot. He\u2019s got the ability to play in the team\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bournemouthecho.co.uk/sport/17652851.eddie-howe-insists-afc-bournemouth-left-back-diego-rico-has-the-ability-to-play-in-the-premier-league|title=Eddie Howe insists AFC Bournemouth left-back Diego Rico has the ability to play in the Premier League|newspaper=[[Bournemouth Daily Echo]]|first=Jason|last=Lewis|date=21 May 2019|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref> \n\nRico enjoyed a much more positive start to [[2019\u201320 Premier League|the following campaign]], making 14 consecutive starts for the team, beginning with a 3\u20131 home win against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49624220|title=AFC Bournemouth 3\u20131 Everton|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Neil|last=Johnston|date=15 September 2019|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref> In October 2019, he was voted Player of the Month for the previous month in a poll conducted by the club's website, playing every minute in the league and also providing two [[Assist (association football)|assists]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.afcb.co.uk/news/first-team/rico-wins-september-player-of-the-month/|title=Rico wins September Player of the Month|publisher=A.F.C. Bournemouth|date=3 October 2019|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nRico is praised for his dead-ball delivery and the quality of his [[Set piece (football)|set-pieces]], and is usually assigned the role of [[Corner kick|corner]] and [[Free kick (association football)|direct free kick]] taker on the pitch. Bournemouth teammate [[Callum Wilson (footballer, born 1992)|Callum Wilson]] described him as having a \"wand of a left foot\", and Howe commented that \"someone with that strength of foot, he has real power in it, accuracy with it and it is a big asset.\u201d<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bournemouthecho.co.uk/sport/cherries/clubnews/17909086.magical-diego-rico-39-s-39-wand-left-foot-39-can-39-big-asset-39-afc-bournemouth/|title=Magical Diego Rico's 'wand of a left foot' can be a 'big asset' for AFC Bournemouth|newspaper=Bournemouth Daily Echo|first=Dan|last=Rose|date=17 September 2019|accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nRico is also noted as being an excellent interceptor of the ball, and a generally strong defensive fullback. Late into 2019\u201320, he had the most interceptions of any player in the Premier League with 66.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bournemouthecho.co.uk/sport/18113728.diego-rico-delivering-fans-happiness-relationship-hugo-faria-making-history-cherries/|title=Diego Rico on delivering fans happiness, his relationship with Hugo Faria and making more history at Cherries|newspaper=Bournemouth Daily Echo|first=Dan|last=Rose|date=20 December 2019|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportinglife.com/football/news/pl-the-case-for-the-defence/178752|title=Premier League: The main statistics behind the top defenders this season|publisher=[[Sporting Life (British newspaper)|Sporting Life]]|first=Tom|last=Carnduff|date=30 March 2020|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|9 February 2020}}<ref>{{soccerway|diego-rico-salguero/238788}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[Real Zaragoza B|Zaragoza B]]\n|[[2011\u201312 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2011\u201312]]\n|[[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]]\n|6||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||6||0\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2012\u201313]]\n|Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B\n|11||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2